9
00:00:44,120 --> 00:00:47,240
Oscar Jonsson, you are a doctor in Russian warfare.

10
00:00:47,400 --> 00:00:52,200
Why does Russia go on these civilian goals?

11
00:00:52,360 --> 00:00:56,200
Russia has since October had a strategy to bomb civil targets -

12
00:00:56,360 --> 00:00:59.720
–And civil critical infrastructure. It fulfills several purposes.

13
00:00:59,880 --> 00:01:06,160
One is to make life miserable, one is to terrorize them so that they can give up.

14
00:01:06,320 --> 00:01:09,000
It also sets a military dilemma.

15
00:01:09,160 --> 00:01:12,400
Ukraine can either protect the most important big cities -

16
00:01:12,560 --> 00:01:17,600
- Or the front line, which will be extra important for the counter -offensive.

17
00:01:17,760 --> 00:01:24,800
We have heard that Kiev has good air defense - yet the drones manage to get through.

18
00:01:24,960 --> 00:01:27.560
How to explain it?

19
00:01:27,720 --> 00:01:32,400
An air defense is never 100 percent, but consists of different systems-

20
00:01:32,560 --> 00:01:37,400
- From short-range to medium and very long-range.

21
00:01:37,560 --> 00:01:40,360
The Russian robotic attacks are often a mix.

22
00:01:40,520 --> 00:01:43,720
First it can be exercise robots without explosive charge -

23
00:01:43,880 --> 00:01:46,680
- Or drones, to saturate the air defense systems.

24
00:01:46,840 --> 00:01:50,400
Then you strike with cruise robots with the explosive effect.

25
00:01:50,560 --> 00:01:55,960
An air defense is never 100 percent. And the drones that cost 200,000-

26
00:01:56,120 --> 00:01:59,120
- Don't want to knock out with air defense robots for two million.

27
