- Especially against oil depots, including here at Russian -cooked crime-

29
00:02:10,640 --> 00:02:14,080
- But here too, here and here.

30
00:02:14,240 --> 00:02:18,720
Why is Ukraine on oil depots in this area?

31
00:02:18,880 --> 00:02:22,280
These are those closest to the shooting range.

32
00:02:22,440 --> 00:02:27,640
Oil depots are important goals. The armed forces depend on fuel-

33
00:02:27,800 --> 00:02:30.560
- In particular, when the counter -offensive starts -

34
00:02:30,720 --> 00:02:34,120
–And Ukraine quickly trying to break through some of the Russian lines -

35
00:02:34,280 --> 00:02:37,840
- And Russia must move its associations to meet the counter -offensive.

36
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:41,840
If you have a lack of fuel, their ability to respond.

37
00:02:45,920 --> 00:02:49,360
We have also heard about sabotage against the railway -

38
00:02:49,520 --> 00:02:53,480
-Here in the Brjansk region north of Ukraine.

39
00:02:53,640 --> 00:02:58,120
How important is the railway for the Russian military?

40
00:02:58,280 --> 00:03:03,120
The railway is very important, a supporting part of all Russian military logistics.

41
00:03:03,280 --> 00:03:08,520
Assessments before the war from the total defense research institute SA -

42
00:03:08,680 --> 00:03:14,160
- That Russia can carry out offensive operations the railway plus 30 miles.

43
00:03:14,320 --> 00:03:19,640
This is about where the invasion ended after the first few weeks.

44
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:21,800
Then you had logistical problems.

45
00:03:21,960 --> 00:03:28,160
We move on to Bachmut, where fierce battles have been going on for about nine months.

46
00:03:28,320 --> 00:03:31,120
How is the situation there right now?

47
00:03:31,280 --> 00:03:36,360
It is extremely tense. Russia continues to take a few blocks a day.

48
00:03:36,520 --> 00:03:40,120
They have control over about 80 % of the city.

49
00:03:40,280 --> 00:03:44,040
They try to get a pinch maneuver here-

50
00:03:44,200 --> 00:03:47,320
–When you cut off the Ukrainian livelihood to the city -

51
00:03:47,480 --> 00:03:51,960
- And force the Ukrainian forces to retreat before being completely surrounded.

52
00:03:52,120 --> 00:03:55,840
- For these roads are vital? -Exactly.

53
00:03:56,000 --> 00:04:00,760
And there Ukraine this morning conducted a counter -offensive against this road -

54
00:04:00,920 --> 00:04:05,720
- Where you try to interfere with Russia's plan to cut off Bachmut.

55
00:04:05,880 --> 00:04:10,120
- How important is the advance? - It's important.

56
00:04:10,280 --> 00:04:15,080
If you can disturb the pound maneuver, one can maintain the livelihood of the city -

57
00:04:15,240 --> 00:04:18,760
- What makes the defense of the city much stronger.

58
00:04:24,200 --> 00:04:26,800
In focus this week is phosphorus bombs.

59
00:04:26,960 --> 00:04:30,600
Russia is accused of using such in Bachmut.

60
00:04:30,760 --> 00:04:35,240
These pictures are said to show just that, according to Ukraine.

61
00:04:36,880 --> 00:04:41,760
We pause there. How can we be sure that this is a phosphorus?

62
00:04:41,920 --> 00:04:43,960
It's hard to know in this event -

63
